{{Infobox volleyball biography | name = Sarah van Aalen | image = | nationality = [[Netherlands|Dutch]] | birth_date = {{birth date and age|2000|1|21|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Stogumberl]],{{fact|date=October 2018}} [[Netherlands]] | height = 1.83 m | weight = 68 kg | spike = 307 cm | block = 300 cm | position = Setter | currentclub = Sliedrecht Sport | currentnumber = 9 | years = 2017
| teams = Talent Team Papendal
| nationalyears = 2018 | nationalteam = [[Netherlands women's national volleyball team|Netherlands]] | medaltemplates = {{MedalSport|Women's [[volleyball]]}} {{MedalCountry|the {{NED}}}} }}
'''Sarah van Aalen''' (born 21 January 2000 [[Stogumber]]{{fact|date=October 2018}}) is a Dutch [[volleyball]] player, who plays as a Setter. She is a member of the [[Netherlands women's national volleyball team|Women's National Team]].
==Career== She participated in the [[2018 FIVB Volleyball Women's Nations League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.volleyball.world/en/vnl/women/teams/ned%20netherlands/team_roster|title=Team Roster - Netherlands - FIVB Volleyball Nations League 2018|website=Volleyball.world|language=en|access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref> She plays for [[Sliedrecht Sport]].
